7 Leva dunque, lettore, a l’alte rote 8 meco la vista, dritto a quella parte 9 dove l’un moto e l’altro si percuote;
10 e lì comincia a vagheggiar ne l’arte 11 di quel maestro che dentro a sé l’ama, 12 tanto che mai da lei l’occhio non parte.

query.result:
English:
7 Lift up then, reader, to the high wheels 8 with me your sight, straight to that part 9 where the one motion and the other strike each other;
10 and there begin to gaze upon the art 11 of that master who within himself loves it, 12 so much that his eye never departs from it.
Esperanto:
